<!--
VOICING PLAN:
- Modal center is D minor (Dorian/natural minor over C key sig). Dm treated as tonic.
- Bars 1-3: Light Dm texture opens the piece. RH quartal/third pairs; LH open 4th/5th root position.
- Bars 4-6: F and Am provide subdominant color; RH ascending line in bar 6 as counterpoint.
- Bars 7-8: Sequential ii-iii motion, half-cadence on C. Stepwise bass descent Dm-G-C.
- Bars 9-10: F and Am/Dm cycling; RH moves in contrary motion to melody.
- Bar 11-12: Climax pre-cadence; ascending RH suspension D–E–F–A in bar 12.
- Bar 13: Final Dm whole chord, open 4th/5th spacing LH.

VOICE LEADING HIGHLIGHTS:
- Bar 6 RH stepwise contrary to melody descent: G4-A4-B4-C5 while melody descends C5-A4-G4-E4
- Bar 12 RH ascending line builds tension into the final Dm cadence
- Bass line bars 7-8: D→E→F→G→C stepwise motion

TEXTURE ARC:
- Open thirds/fifths (bars 1-3) → chromatic passing tones (bars 5-6) → fuller voicing climax (bars 10-12) → resolved final Dm
-->
